{{For|other people called John Rothwell|John Rothwell (disambiguation){{!}}John Rothwell}} {{Infobox scientist |name = John C. Rothwell | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1954}}<ref name=LibraryOfCongress>{{LCAuth|n85351086|John C. Rothwell||}}</ref> |image = JohnRothwell.jpg |caption = John Rothwell at the ''Third International Conference on [[Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation|Transcranial Magnetic]] and [[Transcranial direct current stimulation|Direct Current Stimulation]]'' in [[Göttingen]], 2008 | field = [[Neurophysiology]] | workplaces = [[University College London]] | thesis_title = The function of the human long-latency stretch reflex | thesis_year = 1980 | thesis_url=http://ethos.bl.uk/OrderDetails.do?uin=uk.bl.ethos.258049 | doctoral_advisor = [[C David Marsden]] | alma_mater = [[University of Cambridge]] (BA), [[King's College London]] (PhD) | website = {{URL|http://www.ion.ucl.ac.uk/departments/sobell/Research/JRothwell}} }} '''John C. Rothwell''' (born 1954)<ref name=LibraryOfCongress/> is a [[Professor]] of [[neurophysiology]] at the [[UCL Institute of Neurology]]. His main area of interest is transcranial magnetic stimulation and motor control.<ref name=ucl>{{cite web|first=John|last=Rothwell|year=2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628232129/http://www.ucl.ac.uk/ion/departments/sobell/Research/JRothwell|archivedate=2011-06-28|url=http://www.ucl.ac.uk/ion/departments/sobell/Research/JRothwell|website=ucl.ac.uk|publisher=University College London|location=London|title=Prof. J. Rothwell: Physiology and Pathophysiology of Human Motor Control}}</ref>
==Education== Rothwell was educated at the [[University of Cambridge]]. He completed his [[PhD]] at [[King's College London]] in 1980<ref>{{cite thesis|degree=PhD|publisher=King's College London (University of London)|title=The function of the human long-latency stretch reflex|first= John C.|last=Rothwell|date=1980|url=http://ethos.bl.uk/OrderDetails.do?uin=uk.bl.ethos.258049|oclc=59952890}}</ref> which supervised by [[C David Marsden|David Marsden]].<ref name=rsbm>{{cite journal|last1=Quinn|first1=Niall|last2=Rothwell|first2=John|authorlink2=John Rothwell (physiologist)|last3=Jenner|first3=Peter|title=Charles David Marsden. 15 April 1938 -- 29 September 1998|journal=[[Biographical Memoirs of Fellows of the Royal Society]]|volume=58|issue=0|year=2012|pages=203–228|publisher=[[Royal Society]]|location=London|doi=10.1098/rsbm.2012.0026}}</ref>
==Career and research== His group has pioneered the use of the paired-pulse technique (Kujirai et al. 1992){{specify|date=October 2016}}, interhemispheric studies (Ferbert et al. 1992).{{specify|date=October 2016}}
Rothwell was appointed head of the [[Medical Research Council (United Kingdom)|Medical Research Council (MRC)]] Human Movement and Balance Unit after the untimely death of David Marsden. He has written over 400 papers and numerous chapters.<ref name=scopus>{{Scopus|id=55455767400}}</ref><ref name="RossiniBarker1994">{{cite journal|last1=Rossini|first1=P.M.|last2=Barker|first2=A.T.|last3=Berardelli|first3=A.|last4=Caramia|first4=M.D.|last5=Caruso|first5=G.|last6=Cracco|first6=R.Q.|last7=Dimitrijević|first7=M.R.|last8=Hallett|first8=M.|last9=Katayama|first9=Y.|last10=Lücking|first10=C.H.|last11=Maertens de Noordhout|first11=A.L.|last12=Marsden|first12=C.D.|last13=Murray|first13=N.M.F.|last14=Rothwell|first14=J.C.|last15=Swash|first15=M.|last16=Tomberg|first16=C.|title=Non-invasive electrical and magnetic stimulation of the brain, spinal cord and roots: basic principles and procedures for routine clinical application. Report of an IFCN committee|journal=Electroencephalography and Clinical Neurophysiology|volume=91|issue=2|year=1994|pages=79–92|doi=10.1016/0013-4694(94)90029-9}}</ref><ref name=KujiraiCaramia1993>{{cite journal|last1=Kujirai|first1=T|last2=Caramia|first2=M D|last3=Rothwell|first3=J C|last4=Day|first4=B L|last5=Thompson|first5=P D|last6=Ferbert|first6=A|last7=Wroe|first7=S|last8=Asselman|first8=P|last9=Marsden|first9=C D|title=Corticocortical inhibition in human motor cortex.|journal=The Journal of Physiology|volume=471|issue=1|year=1993|pages=501–519|pmid=8120818|pmc=1143973|doi=10.1113/jphysiol.1993.sp019912}} {{open access}}</ref>
