{{more citations needed|date=February 2013}} {{Infobox person |name = Nicolae Filip |image = Nicolae_Filip_1926.jpg |alt = |caption = |birth_date = {{Birth date|1926|03|03}} |birth_place = Sofia, [[Bălți County (Romania)|Bălți County]], [[Kingdom of Romania]] |death_date = {{Death date and age|2009|05|15|1926|03|03}} |death_place = [[Bălți]], [[Moldova]] |other_names = |known_for = |occupation = [[Physicist]] |nationality = [[Moldova]] }}
'''Nicolae Filip''' (March 3, 1926 &ndash; 15 May 2009) was born in the village of Sofia, [[Bălți]] to a family of farmers. He was an expert in the field of physics, and contributed significantly to the study of "The spread of ultrashort radio waves." He was elected an honorary member of the [[Academy of Sciences of Moldova]].<ref>[http://www.asm.md/?go=detalii-membri&n=132&new_language=0] Detalii despre membrii Academiei de Ştiințe a Moldovei</ref>
He was the Chancellor of [[Bălți]]'s [[Alecu Russo State University of Bălți|State University "Alecu Russo"]].
== Career == * Doctor of Physical and Mathematical Sciences (1962). * Habilitirovanny Doctor of Physical and Mathematical Sciences (1979). * University Professor (1980), a leading specialist in the field of radio physics. * Excellence in Public Education of the USSR (1971). * 1973 awarded the title "Honored Worker of Higher School of MSSR. * 1995 was elected an honorary member of the Academy of Sciences of Moldova. * 1996 awarded the State Prize of the Republic of Moldova in the field of science and technology. * Since 1997, ND Philippe member of the International Academy of Sciences Graduate School. * 2000 [[Honorary Doctor]] Jassy Technical University. Gh.Asachi. * Since 2001, is an honorary citizen of the city [[Bălți|Belts]].
== Awards == * Order "[[Order of Work Merit (Moldova)|Order of Work Merit]]", 1995 * Order "[[Order of the Republic (Moldova)|Order of the Republic]]", 2001
[[Bălți]] Municipal Council Decision Nr. 11/24 on 03.04.2001, the recorded in the Book of Honor by assigning him the title "Honorary Citizen mun. Bălți."
